    "30487027": {
      "title": "miR-155* mediates suppressive effect of PTEN 3'-untranslated region on AP-1/NF-\u03baB pathway in HTR-8/SVneo cells",
      "abstract": "Abstract Among miRNAs, miR-155 is a known regulator of immune system. Accumulating studies have revealed the connections between miR-155 and activator protein 1 (AP-1)/nuclear factor (NF)-\u03baB. However, miR-155*, a miR-155 paralog, has so far been less studied. Here we demonstrated that miR-155*, induced by lipopolysaccharide (LPS) in an AP-1/NF-\u03baB dependent manner, played a positive feedback role in AP-1/NF-\u03baB pathway via targeting interleukin-1 receptor-associated kinase M (IRAKM) and NF-\u03baB inhibitor interacting Ras-like 1 (NKIRAS1) in trophoblasts. Our study further proved that miR-155*-targeted PTEN 3\u2032-untranslated region (3\u2032UTR) increased IRAKM and NKIRAS1 expression by competing for miR-155* binding, thereby suppressing AP-1/NF-\u03baB activation induced by LPS."
    }
  }
}